    <p>
      A SneakyNote URL provides 160-bit security. Your secret is encrypted with 256-bit <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advanced_Encryption_Standard">AES</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CCM_mode">CCM mode</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      We make sure your message never touches a hard disk. And when a SneakyNote is read or expires, we thoroughly erase it from memory.
    </p>


Why no password?